      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:18:5",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) لَا يُقْتَلُ الْوَالِدُ بِوَلَدِهِ وَ يُقْتَلُ الْوَلَدُ بِوَالِدِهِ وَ لَا يَرِثُ الرَّجُلُ الرَّجُلَ إِذَا قَتَلَهُ وَ إِنْ كَانَ خَطَأً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali, from Muhammad Bin Isa, from Yunus, from Ibn Sinan, from Al A’la Bin Al Fuzayl who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The father would not be killed due to his son, but the son would be killed due to (killing of) his father; and the man would not inherit the man when he kills him, even though it (were to) be in error’."
        ]
      }
    },
